      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Lesley Cowley was first appointed non-executive chairperson of DVLA in October 2014 and was re-appointed in October 2016. She was appointed a non-executive director of aql in October 2014 and lead non-executive director of The National Archives in January 2016  She was appointed non-executive chairperson of Companies House in March 2017.</p>

<h2 id="education">Education</h2>

<p>Lesley has a masters degree in Business Administration (MBA) with distinction in 1997 from Bristol Business School, University of the West of England. She completed the senior executive programme at Ashridge Business School in 2014. In 2015, she was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Technology by University of the West of England.  This was in recognition of her achievement and influence in the field of technology. She has been recognised for her contribution to science, technology, engineering and mathematics (STEM) and STEM ambassadors in schools.</p>

<h2 id="career">Career</h2>

<p>Lesley was made an OBE for services to the Internet and e-commerce in 2011. She was previously CEO of Nominet, a role she held from 2004 to 2014. She also served as ICANN ccNSO chair and as a member of the UK Government Cyber Crime Reduction Partnership.</p>

</div>
      </section>

